How Each Library Is Used
1. Pandas
Used to load and manage resume datasets.

import pandas as pd
df = pd.read_csv("resumes.csv")
print(df.head())


2. NumPy
Used for numerical calculations.

import numpy as np
scores = np.array([0.85, 0.76, 0.91])
print(scores.mean())


3. Matplotlib
Used to create graphs and charts.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.plot([1,2,3], [4,5,6])
plt.title("Resume Scores")
plt.show()


4. Seaborn
Used for advanced data visualization.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
sns.histplot([70,80,90,85])
plt.show()


5. Scikit-learn
Used for TF-IDF vectorization and similarity calculation

from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer
from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity


